column5: Fished yesterday and the fish were on fire. Muskies were on wind swept island points with pencil reeds and phragmites in combination with rock. Nothing on main land points that looked similar. Walleye were in 19 to 21 ft on mainland points. Awesome day. Fished in the area south of the Barrier Islands and on the west side of the lake.

What were you using? I fished NE side of LOW on saturday and it seemed it had to be spinners to get them to bite. Very few bites on jigs. We wanted to get to the area south of battier islands but too windy.
